headline: Is Analog Devices Still Attractive After Strong Year to Date Gains in 2025?
summary: If you’ve got Analog Devices on your watchlist and are wondering whether now’s a smart time to buy, hold, or take profits, you’re not alone. The stock has seen its fair share of movement lately, and there are a few layers to unpack before making your next move. In the last week, shares ticked up by 1.6%, adding a bit of optimism to the mix. That’s on top of a robust 14.3% gain year-to-date, and a long-term return of 111.5% over five years.
